Dialogue: 1,0:02:18.07,0:02:24.03,EP Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(1000,0)\be1}The White Which Lives Within the Ink Stone
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.52,0:02:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.44,0:02:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, I need you to come over!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.51,0:02:38.17,Alt,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.17,0:02:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.65,0:02:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,My daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.10,0:02:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When it became evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.98,0:02:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,she suddenly started complaining \Nabout how cold she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.73,0:02:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The boys next door who were playing \Nwith her have the same symptoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.33,0:03:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What's going on? Her body temperature is really low.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.60,0:03:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy, I'm cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.95,0:03:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I want another blanket.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.81,0:03:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.30,0:03:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even her breath is chilled.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.98,0:03:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.41,0:03:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ice?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.69,0:03:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.24,0:03:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We went into your storage shed today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.74,0:03:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So you touched something in the shed?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.53,0:03:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. There was an inkstone...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.21,0:03:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,An inkstone...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.09,0:03:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.22,0:03:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, over here, Ginko.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.31,0:03:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.75,0:03:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I was careless.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.05,0:04:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I was trying not to let the villagers see what was inside my storage shed, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.05,0:04:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How are the patients?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.01,0:04:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They're getting weaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.86,0:04:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to keep their body temperatures up \Nby having them drink hot water, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.68,0:04:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.40,0:04:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I bought it from a collector I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.02,0:04:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks beautiful but moreover,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.56,0:04:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that it's made from \Nsome kind of fossilized mushi, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.45,0:04:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Fossilized Mushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.99,0:04:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if there's such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.74,0:04:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, mushi don't leave a body behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.38,0:04:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't buy things that have \Nunsure backgrounds like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.81,0:04:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Troublemaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.18,0:04:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you forgotten that the things\Nyou cherish are unusual?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.64,0:04:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry... I was careless...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.64,0:04:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't... a fossil.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.53,0:05:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The mushi seem to still be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.90,0:05:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And what were the patients doing at the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.55,0:05:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you do with the inkstone?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.10,0:05:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1598)}We decided to rub an ink stick on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.03,0:05:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.51,0:05:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that? It's just an ordinary inkstone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.11,0:05:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm sure it's a special inkstone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.25,0:05:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, there's some water over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.16,0:05:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try and rub an ink stick on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.81,0:05:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't! The doctor will be mad at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.24,0:05:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.76,0:05:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.98,0:05:38.23,Alt,,0,0,0,, Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.23,0:05:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you guys feel something cold come out of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.22,0:05:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I breathed it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.65,0:05:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The mushi comes alive when ink stick is rubbed, enters the body and chill them from inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.26,0:05:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to identify the mushi\N only knowing these conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.71,0:05:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.50,0:06:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't the previous owner know anything about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.50,0:06:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No. He knows nothing more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.43,0:06:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The people who owned the inkstone \Nbefore that all used it and... died, I hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.32,0:06:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Then our last resort is the maker of the inkstone...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.27,0:06:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an inscription. If you look into it,\N I'm sure you can find the maker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.96,0:06:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.65,0:06:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm taking this with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.87,0:06:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.85,0:06:29.53,Alt,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.17,0:06:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I sure came a long ways up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.44,0:06:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be around here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.56,0:06:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she lives over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.37,0:07:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But she no longer makes inkstones.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.48,0:07:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.47,0:07:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.05,0:07:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,She just quit all of a sudden...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.24,0:07:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't have any relatives left... \Nbut she was really skilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.69,0:07:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.17,0:07:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you the one who made this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.59,0:07:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed... this is my inscription.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.01,0:07:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.55,0:07:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There are children suffering right now \Nbecause of this inkstone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.00,0:07:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to tell me what you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.04,0:08:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks... for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.54,0:08:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I was looking for it... this inkstone...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.64,0:08:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,all this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.93,0:08:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as I know... there are three\N who used that inkstone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.30,0:08:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear they all died within a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.14,0:08:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It all started...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.18,0:08:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,soon after my father, who was a \Nnotable inkstone craftsman, fell ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.89,0:08:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a fiancé.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.82,0:08:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He was my father's client who lived in a town one mountain's crossing away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.45,0:08:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Both he and his parents were opposed to my succeeding my father's work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.83,0:08:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Tagane, you want to do it no matter what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.17,0:08:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You of all people should know...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.01,0:08:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,My father and I are the only ones \Nwho can carve rocks around here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.09,0:09:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to give it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.92,0:09:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't be able to continue alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.41,0:09:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the orders have been falling.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.27,0:09:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In time... I'll create an inkstone as good as my father's.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.59,0:09:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.46,0:09:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.75,0:09:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}lf... I could create an inkstone \Nthat my fiancé would acknowledge,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.23,0:09:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}he would surely...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.25,0:09:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Thereafter, I submerged myself in inkstone making.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.54,0:09:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,2851)}But I had a hard time creating something\N I could be satisfied with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.04,0:09:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, one day, I excavated that rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.47,0:09:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, it enchanted me and\N I began to carve it with fervor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.14,0:09:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The finished inkstone was a masterpiece, \Nthe best I ever made.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.16,0:09:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.27,0:10:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Rub an ink stick on it to test it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.56,0:10:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.68,0:10:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.10,0:10:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,A smoke-like puff came out of the inkstone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.97,0:10:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! It's still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.09,0:10:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.53,0:10:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.93,0:10:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The ink seems to come out fine as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.05,0:10:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I can rest assured now that you can succeed my work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.10,0:11:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Several days have passed after I inhaled that smoke,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.33,0:11:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but it doesn't seem to have affected me,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.66,0:11:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and I was the only one who saw it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.55,0:11:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I hope my fiancé and his parents will \Nreconsider after seeing this inkstone.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.54,0:11:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.80,0:11:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I hold on to this inkstone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.70,0:11:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to try and convince my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.61,0:11:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.10,0:11:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. If they approve, I'll send you a letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.45,0:11:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But the letter that arrived one month later only informed me of my fiancé's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.18,0:11:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He started to complain of chills \Non the day I delivered the inkstone,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.03,0:11:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and he contracted a strange illness that continued to lower his temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.65,0:11:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Saying that the inkstone was a bad omen, his parents sold it to an antiques store.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.80,0:12:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to the store, but it had already been sold,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.53,0:12:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and I lost track of its whereabouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.78,0:12:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But I heard rumors of it from \Na broker and the antiques dealer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.23,0:12:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard another person died because of that inkstone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.45,0:12:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, my father passed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.93,0:12:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and I stopped carving inkstones.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.55,0:12:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to help you, but that's all I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.11,0:12:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, actually, I've now got a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.69,0:12:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.21,0:12:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.74,0:12:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I'm in a hurry, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.53,0:12:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.57,0:12:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you let me buy back that inkstone?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.56,0:12:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to destroy it with my own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.99,0:12:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.75,0:12:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If you like, you can come along with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.25,0:13:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you forgotten that the things \Nyou cherish are unusual?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.73,0:13:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I was aware of it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.93,0:13:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like it's struck home hard, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.56,0:13:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.58,0:13:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better have found something \Nif you're cracking jokes like— that—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.85,0:13:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. We'll definitely be able to save the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.87,0:13:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Charcoal, a stove... and what else?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.47,0:13:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A pot. And also, do you've \Na wooden-framed backpack?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.37,0:13:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.25,0:13:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The mushi inside that inkstone is called {\i1}Kumohami.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.25,0:13:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs40\b0\bord2.5\fad(50,50)\pos(640,30.667)}{\i1}Note:- kumo = cloud, hami = to eat{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.92,0:14:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They've the shape of a cumulonimbus cloud,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.14,0:14:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and, like their name, they eat clouds... in other words, the water and ice in the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.34,0:14:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and makes it rain down snow and hail.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.82,0:14:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you see hail fall at times \Neven when there isn't a cloud visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.04,0:14:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But they can't move on their {\i1}own;{\i0} \Nthey're affected by other factors.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.78,0:14:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,When there's a long period of time without any clouds,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.61,0:14:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,they become condensed and then, they come down to earth and freeze into suspended animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.92,0:14:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, they must've turned into stone... after eons.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.76,0:14:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, they reappeared on the surface of the earth in the form of an inkstone,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.24,0:14:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and were able to come alive again \Nwhenever water was applied to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.73,0:14:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So what are we going to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.95,0:14:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Tagane-san, you said you crossed a mountain when you deliver the inkstone, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.15,0:14:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's probably why you weren't \Naffected by the smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.14,0:14:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll take the patients to the\N highest mountain in these parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.73,0:15:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not good. Give her some hot water.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.17,0:15:13.72,Alt,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.68,0:15:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the water is getting cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.97,0:15:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go on ahead and start boiling water.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.19,0:15:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.30,0:15:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, do we still have to climb further?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.00,0:15:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm having a hard time breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.33,0:15:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And it seems difficult on the children, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.89,0:15:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.03,0:15:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.05,0:16:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone! Hold your breath!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.39,0:16:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! You got your color back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.23,0:16:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not cold anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.25,0:16:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Her temperature is going back to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.65,0:17:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mushi... made it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.26,0:17:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.72,0:17:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Just how... on earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.55,0:17:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the air pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.93,0:17:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The mushi live within the same stratum of the atmosphere where the clouds are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.66,0:17:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It follows that they've the same\N weight as that stratum.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.12,0:17:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they'll be drawn to it if they get\N closer to that altitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.77,0:17:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You live in a high altitude village,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.26,0:17:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so the smoke you inhaled probably \Nescaped you little by little.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.85,0:17:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you crossed the mountain\N to deliver the inkstone,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.19,0:17:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the mushi completely left your body, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.36,0:17:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.09,0:17:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.50,0:18:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wrong to have an interest in dangerous objects like this in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.60,0:18:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take responsibility and destroy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.37,0:18:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said, we now know how to handle it if it happens again, so it shouldn't be a problem anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.53,0:18:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,With that optimistic attitude of yours,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.56,0:18:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,how can you know that everything else here is safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.84,0:18:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's none of your business.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.53,0:18:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ginko. You tell her, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.32,0:18:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Destroying the inkstone means killing \Nthe dormant mushi in there, too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.35,0:18:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... well, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.43,0:18:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You see? The mushi are innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.04,0:18:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, that inkstone is too beautiful to destroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.07,0:18:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think of it as your own child?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.24,0:18:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.92,0:19:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't forgive yourself for making an inkstone that has dormant mushi in it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.26,0:19:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, why don't you just release \Nthe mushi from the inkstone?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.58,0:19:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.21,0:19:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! That's my inkstone you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.65,0:19:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You've a quite bit of the responsibility,\NAdashino, for what just happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.13,0:19:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Er...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.12,0:19:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Just think of it as a lesson learned\N and turn the other cheek.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.17,0:19:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, it's a first-rate inkstone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.31,0:19:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can use it to your heart's content.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.13,0:20:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What the?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.40,0:20:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.22,0:20:34.72,Alt,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.72,0:20:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.72,0:20:35.92,Alt,,0,0,0,,It's hail!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.25,0:20:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's not a cloud in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.83,0:20:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's it coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.67,0:20:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, the repair cost of the roofs \Nin the village is going to be huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.19,0:21:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can bill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.03,0:21:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll repay it even if it takes me a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.70,0:21:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And how are you going to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.51,0:21:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You can start making inkstones again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.66,0:21:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you can reestablish yourself right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.40,0:21:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.67,0:21:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I put in an order for one, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.45,0:21:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind if mine has mushi in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.14,0:21:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You just can't give it up, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.27,0:21:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.28,0:21:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,...although I think it'll take a little time to deliver it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.54,0:21:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, when is this going to stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.19,0:21:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The mushi probably haven't eaten in ages, so...
